271
00:20:23.598 --> 00:20:25.600
You're very difficult for me to read.

272
00:20:25.683 --> 00:20:27.394
Hey, did you get contacts?

273
00:20:28.395 --> 00:20:29.813
No.

274
00:20:30.855 --> 00:20:33.024
Your eyes were black
the last time I saw you,

275
00:20:33.108 --> 00:20:37.070
and now they're, like, golden brown.

276
00:20:37.153 --> 00:20:41.533
Yeah, I know, it's the...
It's the fluorescents.

277
00:21:37.130 --> 00:21:38.756
- Bella!
- Bella!

278
00:21:40.467 --> 00:21:41.759
- Dial 911!
- I already called.

279
00:21:41.843 --> 00:21:43.279
They're gonna send
somebody over soon.

280
00:21:43.303 --> 00:21:45.263
Bella, I'm so sorry. I panicked.

281
00:21:46.890 --> 00:21:49.225
Bella, I've got 911 on the phone now.

282
00:21:55.732 --> 00:21:58.443
Bella. You okay?

283
00:21:58.526 --> 00:22:00.086
You and I are gonna talk.
You all right?

284
00:22:00.153 --> 00:22:01.779
I'm fine, Dad. Calm down.

285
00:22:01.863 --> 00:22:04.365
I'm sorry, Bella. I tried to stop.

286
00:22:04.449 --> 00:22:05.533
I know. It's okay.

287
00:22:05.617 --> 00:22:08.369
No. It sure as hell is not okay.

288
00:22:08.453 --> 00:22:09.537
Dad, it wasn't his fault.

289
00:22:09.621 --> 00:22:11.664
You could've been killed.
You understand that?

290
00:22:11.748 --> 00:22:14.000
Yes. But I wasn't, so...

291
00:22:15.001 --> 00:22:16.503
You can kiss your license goodbye.

292
00:22:17.670 --> 00:22:19.790
- I heard the chief's daughter was here.
- Dr. Cullen.

293
00:22:19.839 --> 00:22:22.133
Charlie.

294
00:22:22.217 --> 00:22:23.676
I've got this one, Jackie.

295
00:22:25.386 --> 00:22:27.889
- Isabella.
- Bella.

296
00:22:28.890 --> 00:22:31.768
Well, Bella, looks like you took
quite a spill. How do you feel?

297
00:22:31.851 --> 00:22:32.852
Good.

298
00:22:33.853 --> 00:22:35.230
Look here.

299
00:22:36.231 --> 00:22:40.235
You might experience some
post-traumatic stress or disorientation,

300
00:22:40.318 --> 00:22:42.195
but your vitals look good.

301
00:22:42.278 --> 00:22:45.990
No signs of any head trauma.
I think you'll be just fine.

302
00:22:46.074 --> 00:22:47.909
I'm so sorry, Bella. I'm really...

303
00:22:51.079 --> 00:22:53.557
You know, it would've been a whole lot
worse if Edward wasn't there.

304
00:22:53.581 --> 00:22:55.833
He knocked me out of the way.

305
00:22:55.917 --> 00:22:57.961
Edward? Your boy?

306
00:22:58.044 --> 00:22:59.754
Yeah, it was amazing.

307
00:22:59.837 --> 00:23:02.882
I mean, he got to me so fast.
He was nowhere near me.

308
00:23:02.966 --> 00:23:04.634
Sounds like you were very lucky.

309
00:23:04.717 --> 00:23:06.261
Charlie.

310
00:23:10.431 --> 00:23:12.684
I gotta go sigh some paperwork.
You should...

311
00:23:14.269 --> 00:23:16.688
You should probably call your mom.

312
00:23:16.771 --> 00:23:18.356
Did you tell her?

313
00:23:21.276 --> 00:23:25.321
She's probably just freaking out.

314
00:23:26.823 --> 00:23:28.575
...fifteen kids that saw what happened.

315
00:23:28.658 --> 00:23:31.202
What was I supposed
to do, then? Let her die?

316
00:23:31.286 --> 00:23:33.997
This isn't just about you.
It's about all of us.

317
00:23:34.080 --> 00:23:35.790
I think we should take this in my office.

318
00:23:38.710 --> 00:23:39.770
Can I talk to you for a minute?

319
00:23:39.794 --> 00:23:41.504
Rosalie.

320
00:23:47.969 --> 00:23:49.012
What?

321
00:23:51.014 --> 00:23:55.059
How did you get over to me so fast?

322
00:23:55.143 --> 00:23:56.811
I was standing right next to you, Bella.

323
00:23:57.812 --> 00:24:01.524
No. You were next to your car,
across the lot.

324
00:24:01.608 --> 00:24:03.276
No, I wasn't.

325
00:24:06.154 --> 00:24:09.324
Yes, you were.

326
00:24:09.407 --> 00:24:13.911
Bella, you're-- You hit your head.
I think you're confused.

327
00:24:13.995 --> 00:24:15.788
I know what I saw.

328
00:24:15.872 --> 00:24:17.915
And what exactly was that?

329
00:24:19.167 --> 00:24:20.335
You...

330
00:24:22.253 --> 00:24:24.672
You stopped the van.

331
00:24:24.756 --> 00:24:26.966
You pushed it away with your hand.

332
00:24:28.384 --> 00:24:30.303
Well, nobody's
gonna believe you, so...

333
00:24:32.388 --> 00:24:37.644
I wasn't gonna tell anybody.
I just need to know the truth.

334
00:24:38.645 --> 00:24:41.856
Can't you just thank me
and get over it?

335
00:24:41.939 --> 00:24:43.483
Thank you.

336
00:24:44.901 --> 00:24:46.701
- You're not gonna let this go, are you?
- No.

337
00:24:47.695 --> 00:24:49.739
Well, then I hope you
enjoy disappointment.

338
00:25:25.191 --> 00:25:27.735
And that was the first night
I dreamt of Edward Cullen.

339
00:25:31.114 --> 00:25:32.824
I need everybody's
permission slips, okay?

340
00:25:32.907 --> 00:25:34.659
- Sammy, please collect them.
- Yeah.

341
00:25:34.742 --> 00:25:38.371
Guys, let's go.
Come on, get in. In. Let's go!

342
00:25:51.592 --> 00:25:54.846
Look at you, huh?
You're alive!

343
00:25:54.929 --> 00:25:57.473
- I know, yeah. False alarm, I guess.
- Yeah.

344
00:25:57.557 --> 00:26:01.519
Now, I wanted to ask you,
you know, if, you know,

345
00:26:01.602 --> 00:26:03.271
it's like a month away, but...

346
00:26:05.022 --> 00:26:08.776
Do you wanna go to prom with me?

347
00:26:11.696 --> 00:26:13.656
So, what do you think?

348
00:26:13.740 --> 00:26:15.283
About what?

349
00:26:15.366 --> 00:26:20.246
Do you want to go?
To prom?

350
00:26:20.329 --> 00:26:21.831
With me?

351
00:26:23.207 --> 00:26:26.335
Oh, I... Prom.

352
00:26:27.628 --> 00:26:29.505
Dancing.

353
00:26:29.589 --> 00:26:33.426
Not such a good idea for me.

354
00:26:33.509 --> 00:26:35.845
I have something
that weekend anyway.

355
00:26:35.928 --> 00:26:37.972
I'm going to Jacksonville
that weekend.

356
00:26:38.055 --> 00:26:41.309
- You can't go another weekend??
- Non-refundable ticket.

357
00:26:42.643 --> 00:26:45.938
You should ask Jessica.
I know she wants to go with you.

358
00:26:46.939 --> 00:26:48.649
All right. All right.

359
00:26:49.776 --> 00:26:51.277
Yo, yo, yo.
Hey, guys, come on.

360
00:26:52.278 --> 00:26:53.654
We gotta go. We gotta go.

361
00:26:53.738 --> 00:26:55.448
Green is what? Good.

362
00:26:55.531 --> 00:26:57.408
Let's go. Guys, come on.

363
00:26:59.410 --> 00:27:01.078
Other bus, other bus.
Let's go.

364
00:27:01.162 --> 00:27:02.663
Eggshells, carrot tops.

365
00:27:02.747 --> 00:27:05.416
Compost is cool.
Now, stuff that in there, Eric.

366
00:27:05.500 --> 00:27:07.019
- Yes, sir. Yes, Sir.
- Very good, very good.

367
00:27:07.043 --> 00:27:12.673
Now, I am gonna make a steaming cup of
compost tea.

368
00:27:12.757 --> 00:27:13.841
- Okay.
- Give me that.

369
00:27:13.925 --> 00:27:17.804
Yeah. This is recycling
in its most basic form, guys.

370
00:27:17.887 --> 00:27:21.098
Don't drink it!
It's for the plants.

371
00:27:21.182 --> 00:27:22.517
What's in Jacksonville?

372
00:27:25.228 --> 00:27:26.771
How do you know about that?

373
00:27:28.523 --> 00:27:30.900
You didn't answer my question.

374
00:27:30.983 --> 00:27:33.736
You don't answer any of mine, so...

375
00:27:33.820 --> 00:27:35.446
I mean, you don't even say hi to me.

376
00:27:36.864 --> 00:27:37.865
Hi.

377
00:27:39.742 --> 00:27:42.328
Are you gonna tell me
how you stopped the van?

378
00:27:42.411 --> 00:27:45.790
Yeah. I had an adrenaline rush.

379
00:27:45.873 --> 00:27:48.668
It's very common.
You can Google it.

380
00:27:52.380 --> 00:27:55.508
Floridians.
That's what's in Jacksonville.

381
00:27:57.051 --> 00:27:58.928
Can you at least
watch where you walk?

382
00:28:02.807 --> 00:28:06.561
Look, I'm sorry I'm being rude all
the time. I just think it's the best way.

383
00:28:06.644 --> 00:28:09.814
Bella! Guess who
just asked me to prom?

384
00:28:09.897 --> 00:28:11.649
Who?

385
00:28:11.732 --> 00:28:16.696
Yeah, I actually totally thought
that Mike was gonna ask you.

386
00:28:16.779 --> 00:28:19.949
- It's not gonna be weird, though, right?
- No. Zero weirdness.

387
00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:21.872
- You guys are great together.
- I know, right?

388
00:28:23.035 --> 00:28:24.912
- Tyler...
- Gross.

389
00:28:24.996 --> 00:28:28.791
Bella, look, it's a worm.
It's a worm.

