00:28:32.628 --> 00:28:35.256
Bella, we shouldn't be friends.

391
00:28:37.758 --> 00:28:40.136
You really should've figured
that out a little earlier.

392
00:28:41.929 --> 00:28:43.574
I mean, why didn't you
just let the van crush me

393
00:28:43.598 --> 00:28:45.725
and save yourself all this regret?

394
00:28:48.144 --> 00:28:49.979
What, you think I regret saving you?

395
00:28:50.062 --> 00:28:53.566
I can see that you do.
I just... I don't know why.

396
00:28:54.609 --> 00:28:57.194
You don't know anything.

397
00:28:57.278 --> 00:29:00.114
Hi. Are you gonna be riding with us?

398
00:29:00.197 --> 00:29:01.908
No, our bus is full.

399
00:29:12.126 --> 00:29:14.253
Your mom called. Again.

400
00:29:16.088 --> 00:29:17.089
Well, that's your fault.

401
00:29:17.173 --> 00:29:19.860
You shouldn't have told her about
the "almost" accident. You finished?

402
00:29:19.884 --> 00:29:21.761
Yeah.

403
00:29:21.844 --> 00:29:24.324
Yeah, I suppose you're right.
She always did know how to worry.

404
00:29:27.308 --> 00:29:28.643
She seems different.

405
00:29:30.061 --> 00:29:31.312
- She seems happy.
- Hmm.

406
00:29:35.066 --> 00:29:36.525
Phil sounds like an all right guy.

407
00:29:39.153 --> 00:29:40.905
Yeah, he is.

408
00:29:47.495 --> 00:29:48.537
All right.

409
00:29:48.746 --> 00:29:50.247
No, you need the mitts.
You need them.

410
00:29:51.832 --> 00:29:54.210
No, why do you keep arguing with me?
You just need them.

411
00:29:54.293 --> 00:29:56.253
- You're gonna get frostbite!
- I don't even know.

412
00:30:00.633 --> 00:30:02.176
Yeah. Hey!

413
00:30:02.259 --> 00:30:03.886
La Push, baby. You in?

414
00:30:03.970 --> 00:30:05.072
Should I know what that means?

415
00:30:05.096 --> 00:30:07.616
La Push Beach down at the Quileute Rez.
We're all going tomorrow.

416
00:30:07.640 --> 00:30:08.951
Yeah, there's a big swell coming in.

417
00:30:08.975 --> 00:30:10.893
And I don't just surf the Internet.

418
00:30:10.977 --> 00:30:13.229
Eric, you stood up once,
and it was a foam board.

419
00:30:13.312 --> 00:30:15.481
But there's whale watching, too.
Come with us.

420
00:30:15.564 --> 00:30:18.985
La Push, baby. It's La Push.

421
00:30:19.068 --> 00:30:21.278
Okay, I'll go if you
stop saying that, okay?

422
00:30:21.362 --> 00:30:22.905
Seriously, dude.
It's creepy, man.

423
00:30:22.989 --> 00:30:24.341
- What? That's what it's called.
- So...

424
00:30:24.365 --> 00:30:25.741
Edible art?

425
00:30:29.203 --> 00:30:30.204
Bella.

426
00:30:31.706 --> 00:30:32.915
Thanks.

427
00:30:32.999 --> 00:30:35.835
You know, your mood swings are
kind of giving me whiplash.

428
00:30:38.546 --> 00:30:41.191
I only said it'd be better if we weren't
friends, not that I didn't wanna be.

429
00:30:41.215 --> 00:30:42.800
What does that mean?

430
00:30:44.051 --> 00:30:47.430
It means if you were smart,
you'd stay away from me.

431
00:30:48.431 --> 00:30:51.600
Okay, well, let's say, for argument's
sake, that I'm not smart.

432
00:30:51.684 --> 00:30:53.894
- Would you tell me the truth?
- No, probably not.

433
00:30:55.980 --> 00:30:57.189
I'd rather hear your theories.

434
00:30:59.567 --> 00:31:05.364
I have considered radioactive spiders
and Kryptonite.

435
00:31:07.408 --> 00:31:09.785
That's all superhero stuff, right?

436
00:31:09.869 --> 00:31:13.539
What if I'm not the hero?
What if I'm the bad guy?

437
00:31:13.622 --> 00:31:18.252
You're not. I can see
what you're trying to put off,

438
00:31:18.335 --> 00:31:21.630
but I can see that it's just to keep
people away from you. It's a mask.

439
00:31:26.343 --> 00:31:30.014
Why don't we just hang out?

440
00:31:32.183 --> 00:31:34.894
Everybody's going to the beach. Come.

441
00:31:36.645 --> 00:31:39.899
I mean, have fun.

442
00:31:42.943 --> 00:31:45.279
- Which beach?
- La Push.

443
00:31:45.362 --> 00:31:47.281
I don't know. I just...

444
00:31:49.492 --> 00:31:51.994
Is there something wrong
with that beach?

445
00:31:54.955 --> 00:31:56.457
It's just a little crowded.

446
00:32:02.338 --> 00:32:04.507
- Hey, it's freezing.
- I'm paddling out, Coates.

447
00:32:05.800 --> 00:32:08.445
- I don't know if it's worth it anymore.
- We drove all the way out here.

448
00:32:08.469 --> 00:32:10.262
- I'm at least paddling out.
- Yeah.

449
00:32:10.346 --> 00:32:11.889
- She's right.
- You guys are babies.

450
00:32:11.972 --> 00:32:15.559
So, I keep thinking that Eric's gonna ask
me to the prom,

451
00:32:15.643 --> 00:32:18.187
and then he just doesn't.

452
00:32:20.773 --> 00:32:22.149
You should ask him.

453
00:32:23.734 --> 00:32:27.571
Take control. You're a strong,
independent woman.

454
00:32:27.655 --> 00:32:30.699
- I am?
- Yes.

455
00:32:30.783 --> 00:32:32.535
- Hey, will you do me up?
- Yeah.

456
00:32:34.703 --> 00:32:36.914
- Bella!
- Hi, Jacob.

457
00:32:36.997 --> 00:32:38.642
- Guys, this is Jacob.
- Hey, guys. How you doing?

458
00:32:38.666 --> 00:32:39.792
- Hi.
- Hi.

459
00:32:41.919 --> 00:32:45.339
- What are you, like, stalking me?
- You're on my rez, remember?

460
00:32:47.007 --> 00:32:48.926
Are you surfing?

461
00:32:49.009 --> 00:32:50.845
- Definitely not.
- Thanks.

462
00:32:50.928 --> 00:32:53.556
You guys should keep Bella company.
Her date bailed.

463
00:32:53.639 --> 00:32:56.225
- What date?
- She invited Edward.

464
00:32:56.308 --> 00:32:58.018
To be polite, that's it.

465
00:32:58.102 --> 00:33:00.563
I think it's nice she invited him.
Nobody ever does.

466
00:33:00.646 --> 00:33:03.899
- Yeah, 'cause Cullen's a freak.
- You got that right.

467
00:33:03.983 --> 00:33:05.901
You guys know him?

468
00:33:05.985 --> 00:33:08.070
The Cullens don't come here.

469
00:33:16.704 --> 00:33:20.958
What did your friends mean about, you
know, "The Cullens don't come here?"

470
00:33:21.041 --> 00:33:23.210
You caught that, huh?

471
00:33:24.795 --> 00:33:28.799
I'm not really supposed
to say anything about it.

472
00:33:28.883 --> 00:33:31.594
Hey, I can keep a secret.

473
00:33:33.012 --> 00:33:36.098
Really, it's just like an old scary story.

474
00:33:38.434 --> 00:33:40.352
Well, I want to know.

475
00:33:43.314 --> 00:33:48.444
Okay, did you know Quileutes are
supposedly descended from wolves?

476
00:33:48.527 --> 00:33:50.905
What? Like, wolves?

477
00:33:50.988 --> 00:33:52.068
- Yeah.
- Like, real wolves?

478
00:33:53.032 --> 00:33:56.493
Well, that's the legend of our tribe.

479
00:33:56.577 --> 00:33:57.745
Okay.

480
00:33:57.828 --> 00:33:59.455
So what's the story
about the Cullens?

481
00:34:01.874 --> 00:34:06.003
Well, they're supposedly descended
from this, like, enemy clan.

482
00:34:09.757 --> 00:34:13.135
