Was it other vampires
that killed Waylon?

754
01:00:47.645 --> 01:00:48.646
Yeah.

755
01:00:48.729 --> 01:00:52.858
There are others out there,
and we run into them from time to time.

756
01:00:55.402 --> 01:00:59.031
Can the rest of your family
read people's minds like you can?

757
01:01:02.409 --> 01:01:04.036
No. That's just me.

758
01:01:05.037 --> 01:01:07.915
But Alice-- Alice can see the future.

759
01:01:08.916 --> 01:01:10.584
I bet she saw me coming.

760
01:01:12.253 --> 01:01:15.047
Alice's visions are subjective.

761
01:01:15.130 --> 01:01:17.299
I mean, the future
can always change.

762
01:01:28.352 --> 01:01:31.063
Could you act human?
I mean, I've got neighbors.

763
01:01:31.146 --> 01:01:32.815
I'm gonna take you
to my place tomorrow.

764
01:01:35.484 --> 01:01:38.487
Thanks. Wait,
like, with your family?

765
01:01:39.655 --> 01:01:41.490
Yeah.

766
01:01:41.574 --> 01:01:44.535
What if they don't like me?

767
01:01:44.618 --> 01:01:48.205
So, you're worried not because you'll be
in a house full of vampires,

768
01:01:48.289 --> 01:01:50.374
but because you think
they won't approve of you?

769
01:01:51.709 --> 01:01:53.168
I'm glad I amuse you.

770
01:01:55.170 --> 01:01:56.255
What is it?

771
01:01:58.048 --> 01:01:59.466
Complication.

772
01:02:01.677 --> 01:02:03.304
I'll pick you up tomorrow.

773
01:02:29.538 --> 01:02:32.583
Hey. Come to visit your truck?

774
01:02:33.626 --> 01:02:36.712
- Looks good. Got that dent out.
- Yeah.

775
01:02:36.795 --> 01:02:38.756
Actually, we came to visit
your flat-screen.

776
01:02:38.839 --> 01:02:41.050
First Mariners game of the season.

777
01:02:41.133 --> 01:02:44.845
Plus Jacob here keeps bugging me
about seeing you again.

778
01:02:44.929 --> 01:02:46.722
Great, Dad. Thanks.

779
01:02:46.805 --> 01:02:48.223
Just keeping it real, son.

780
01:02:50.517 --> 01:02:51.769
Vitamin R.

781
01:02:51.852 --> 01:02:54.063
Well done, Chief.

782
01:02:54.146 --> 01:02:56.523
Harry Clear water's homemade fish fry.

783
01:02:56.607 --> 01:02:57.816
Good man.

784
01:03:00.486 --> 01:03:01.946
Any luck with that Waylon case?

785
01:03:02.029 --> 01:03:04.865
Well, I don't think
it was an animal that killed him.

786
01:03:04.949 --> 01:03:06.742
Never thought it was.

787
01:03:08.786 --> 01:03:12.164
So spread the word out at the rez, huh?
Keep the kids out of the woods.

788
01:03:12.247 --> 01:03:14.249
Will do.

789
01:03:14.333 --> 01:03:16.669
Don't want no one else
getting hurt, do we?

790
01:03:47.866 --> 01:03:49.535
Whoa.

791
01:03:51.286 --> 01:03:52.830
This is incredible.

792
01:03:56.166 --> 01:03:58.752
It's so light and open,
you know?

793
01:04:00.462 --> 01:04:04.883
What did you expect,
coffins and dungeons and moats?

794
01:04:04.967 --> 01:04:09.221
- No, not the moats.
- "Not the moats."

795
01:04:16.729 --> 01:04:18.897
This is the one place
we don't have to hide.

796
01:04:22.234 --> 01:04:23.527
I told them not to do this.

797
01:04:23.610 --> 01:04:27.781
You add a little bit of olive oil
to a non-stick sautÃ© pan,

798
01:04:27.865 --> 01:04:31.201
and you want to cook with the olive oil
in medium-high heat.

799
01:04:31.285 --> 01:04:35.080
What I do, I cut this in strips,
and then we gonna cut this in dice.

800
01:04:35.164 --> 01:04:38.292
- Is she even Italian?
- Her name is Bella.

801
01:04:38.375 --> 01:04:40.210
I'm sure she'll love it,
no matter what.

802
01:04:41.462 --> 01:04:43.714
Get a whiff of that.

803
01:04:43.797 --> 01:04:45.841
Here comes the human.

804
01:04:49.803 --> 01:04:52.389
Bella, we're making Italiano for you.

805
01:04:52.473 --> 01:04:55.476
- Oh. Um...
- Bella, this is Esme,

806
01:04:55.559 --> 01:04:57.603
my mother for all
intents and purposes.

807
01:04:57.686 --> 01:04:59.730
- Buon giorno.
- Molto bene.

808
01:05:00.731 --> 01:05:03.043
You've given us an excuse
to use the kitchen for the first time.

809
01:05:03.067 --> 01:05:05.360
- I hope you're hungry.
- Yeah, absolutely.

810
01:05:05.444 --> 01:05:06.445
She already ate.

811
01:05:13.160 --> 01:05:14.161
Perfect.

812
01:05:15.287 --> 01:05:19.291
Yeah, it's just because I know
you guys don't eat...

813
01:05:19.374 --> 01:05:21.835
Of course. It's very considerate of you.

814
01:05:21.919 --> 01:05:24.296
- Just ignore Rosalie. I do.
- Yeah.

815
01:05:24.379 --> 01:05:27.883
Let's just keep pretending
like this isn't dangerous for all of us.

816
01:05:27.966 --> 01:05:31.970
I would never tell
anybody anything.

817
01:05:32.054 --> 01:05:33.806
She knows that.

818
01:05:33.889 --> 01:05:36.975
Yeah, well, the problem is, you two
have gone public now, so...

819
01:05:37.059 --> 01:05:38.936
- Emmett.
- No, she should know.

820
01:05:39.937 --> 01:05:43.982
The entire family will be implicated
if this ends badly.

821
01:05:44.066 --> 01:05:47.319
Badly, as in...

822
01:05:47.402 --> 01:05:49.321
I would become the meal.

823
01:05:57.121 --> 01:05:58.330
Hi, Bella.

824
01:06:02.334 --> 01:06:04.461
I'm Alice.

825
01:06:04.545 --> 01:06:06.421
- Hi.
- Hi.

826
01:06:07.923 --> 01:06:09.842
You do smell good.

827
01:06:09.925 --> 01:06:11.051
Alice, what are you...

828
01:06:11.135 --> 01:06:13.720
It's okay. Bella and I are
gonna be great friends.

829
01:06:17.933 --> 01:06:20.394
Sorry, Jasper's
our newest vegetarian.

830
01:06:20.477 --> 01:06:22.563
It's a little difficult for him.

831
01:06:22.646 --> 01:06:24.523
It's a pleasure to meet you.

832
01:06:24.606 --> 01:06:27.526
It's okay, Jasper.
You won't hurt her.

833
01:06:28.902 --> 01:06:32.531
All right, I'm gonna take you on a tour
of the rest of the house.

834
01:06:32.614 --> 01:06:34.449
- Okay.
- Well, I'll see you soon.

835
01:06:34.533 --> 01:06:36.243
Okay.

836
01:06:38.162 --> 01:06:40.205
- Cute!
- I know.

837
01:06:40.289 --> 01:06:43.917
- I think that went well.
- Clean this up. Now.

838
01:06:44.001 --> 01:06:47.212
Was that as weird for you
as it was for me?

839
01:06:47.296 --> 01:06:48.755
I don't know.

840
01:06:54.720 --> 01:06:57.514
Graduation caps?

841
01:06:57.598 --> 01:07:01.226
Yeah. It's a private joke.

842
01:07:01.310 --> 01:07:02.728
We matriculate a lot.

843
01:07:04.813 --> 01:07:09.610
That's kind of miserable. I mean,
repeating high school over and over.

844
01:07:09.693 --> 01:07:11.778
True, but the younger
we start out in a new place,

845
01:07:11.862 --> 01:07:13.989
the longer we can stay there.

846
01:07:14.072 --> 01:07:15.157
Come on.

847
01:07:25.834 --> 01:07:27.336
Yeah, this is my room.

848
01:07:40.432 --> 01:07:41.433
No bed?

849
01:07:42.517 --> 01:07:46.021
No, I don't... I don't sleep.

850
01:07:47.105 --> 01:07:49.691
- Ever?
- No, not at all.

851
01:07:52.819 --> 01:07:54.071
Okay.

852
01:08:02.537 --> 01:08:04.581
Boy, you have so much music.

853
01:08:05.582 --> 01:08:07.793
What are you listening to?

854
01:08:11.088 --> 01:08:12.881
It's Debussy.

855
01:08:15.259 --> 01:08:16.927
- I don't know...
- Yeah.

856
01:08:20.973 --> 01:08:22.432
Claire De Lune is great.

857
01:08:57.926 --> 01:09:01.346
- What?
- I can't dance.

858
01:09:06.143 --> 01:09:07.394
Hmm...

859
01:09:09.980 --> 01:09:11.732
Well, I could always make you.

860
01:09:14.526 --> 01:09:16.069
I'm not scared of you.

861
01:09:19.906 --> 01:09:21.700
Well, you really
shouldn't have said that.

862
01:09:27.205 --> 01:09:30.042
You better hold on tight,
spider monkey.

863
01:09:35.172 --> 01:09:36.256
Do you trust me?

864
01:09:37.466 --> 01:09:38.633
In theory.

865
01:09:39.634 --> 01:09:40.886
Then close your eyes.

866
01:10:06.078 --> 01:10:07.412
What?

867
01:10:08.413 --> 01:10:10.916
This isn't real.

868
01:10:10.999 --> 01:10:13.585
This kind of stuff just doesn't exist.

869
01:10:13.668 --> 01:10:15.212
It does in my world.

870
01:11:45.343 --> 01:11:46.595
Hold up.

871
01:11:52.100 --> 01:11:53.268
It's human.

872
01:11:57.606 --> 01:12:00.984
Arizona.
Yo, what's happening?

873
01:12:01.067 --> 01:12:03.069
So you and Cullen, huh?

874
01:12:03.153 --> 01:12:05.447
That's... I don't like it.

875
01:12:06.448 --> 01:12:10.202
I mean, I don't know, he just looks at you
like you're something to eat.

876
01:12:14.039 --> 01:12:15.916
Here's your veggie plate, Stephanie.

877
01:12:17.083 --> 01:12:20.712
Hey, sorry I'm late. Biology project.

878
01:12:20.795 --> 01:12:23.673
I ordered you the spinach salad.
I hope that's okay.

879
01:12:23.757 --> 01:12:28.136
You should order one for yourself
next time, cut back on the steak.

880
01:12:28.220 --> 01:12:30.305
Hey, I'm as healthy as a horse.

881
01:12:31.473 --> 01:12:33.600
Say, Chief, boys want to know.

882
01:12:35.393 --> 01:12:38.188
Did you find anything
down by Queets River today?

883
01:12:41.483 --> 01:12:43.902
Yeah, we found
a bare human footprint,

884
01:12:43.985 --> 01:12:46.363
but it looks like whoever that is
is headed east,

885
01:12:46.446 --> 01:12:49.199
so Kitsap County Sheriff
is gonna take over from here.

886
01:12:49.282 --> 01:12:50.617
- Okay.
- Okay?

887
01:12:50.700 --> 01:12:53.495
I just hope they catch him fast.

888
01:13:02.504 --> 01:13:04.104
Looks like your friends
are flagging you.

889
01:13:07.342 --> 01:13:10.845
It's okay if you wanna go join them.
I'm just gonna turn in early anyway.

890
01:13:11.846 --> 01:13:13.223
Me, too.

891
01:13:13.306 --> 01:13:15.392
Bella, it's Friday night. Go out.

892
01:13:16.810 --> 01:13:19.354
Looks like the Newton boy's
got a big smile for you.

893
01:13:19.437 --> 01:13:21.439
Yeah, he's a good buddy.

894
01:13:21.523 --> 01:13:25.652
What about any of these other
yahoos in town? Anybody interest you?

895
01:13:28.154 --> 01:13:29.614
Dad, we're gonna talk about boys?

896
01:13:31.783 --> 01:13:32.951
Yeah, I guess not.

897
01:13:34.202 --> 01:13:37.789
I just feel like I leave you alone
too much.

898
01:13:37.872 --> 01:13:39.874
You should be around people.

899
01:13:41.334 --> 01:13:42.836
I don't really mind being alone.

900
01:13:44.296 --> 01:13:46.590
I guess I'm kind
of like my dad in that way.

901
01:13:51.720 --> 01:13:54.097
So, how's all the baseball stuff going?

902
01:13:54.180 --> 01:13:57.142
Oh, Phil's working so hard.

903
01:13:57.225 --> 01:13:59.644
You know, spring training.

904
01:13:59.728 --> 01:14:02.331
We're looking for a house to rent in case
things become more permanent.

905
01:14:02.355 --> 01:14:05.650
- You'd like Jacksonville, baby.
- Yeah?

906
01:14:05.734 --> 01:14:08.737
- I'm really liking Forks.
- What?

907
01:14:10.739 --> 01:14:12.532
Forks is growing on me.

908
01:14:12.616 --> 01:14:14.367
Could a guy have anything
to do with that?

909
01:14:14.451 --> 01:14:18.997
- Well, yeah.
- I knew it.

910
01:14:19.080 --> 01:14:21.666
Tell me everything.
What is he? Jock? Indie?

911
01:14:21.750 --> 01:14:23.501
I bet he's smart. Is he smart?

912
01:14:26.254 --> 01:14:28.506
Mom, can I talk to you later?

913
01:14:28.590 --> 01:14:30.717
Come on, we gotta talk boys.
Are you being safe?

914
01:14:37.057 --> 01:14:38.266
How did you get in here?

915
01:14:39.392 --> 01:14:41.311
The window.

916
01:14:41.394 --> 01:14:42.937
Do you do that a lot?

917
01:14:44.272 --> 01:14:46.483
Well, just the past couple of months.

918
01:14:50.820 --> 01:14:53.490
I like watching you sleep. It's, um...

919
01:14:55.617 --> 01:14:57.202
It's kind of fascinating to me.

920
01:15:00.163 --> 01:15:01.414
Um...

921
01:15:02.707 --> 01:15:04.501
I always want to try one thing.

922
01:15:06.294 --> 01:15:08.004
Just stay very still.

923
01:15:15.220 --> 01:15:16.596
Don't move.

924
01:16:00.557 --> 01:16:01.766
Stop it!

925
01:16:04.686 --> 01:16:06.104
I'm sorry.

926
01:16:09.023 --> 01:16:10.316
I'm stronger than I thought.

927
01:16:11.818 --> 01:16:13.695
Yeah. I wish
I could say the same.

928
01:16:19.117 --> 01:16:21.244
I can't ever lose control with you.

929
01:16:28.001 --> 01:16:29.544
Hey, don't go.

930
01:17:17.342 --> 01:17:20.011
- Hey, got you another one.
- Thanks.

931
01:17:20.094 --> 01:17:21.888
I have a date with Edward Cullen.

932
01:17:24.766 --> 01:17:26.601
He's a little old for you, isn't he?

933
01:17:27.769 --> 01:17:30.814
No. He's a junior. I'm a junior.

934
01:17:32.440 --> 01:17:33.942
I thought you
liked the Cullens.

935
01:17:35.151 --> 01:17:37.821
I thought you didn't like
any of the boys in town.

936
01:17:37.904 --> 01:17:39.781
Edward doesn't live in town.

937
01:17:40.782 --> 01:17:41.908
Technically.

938
01:17:45.036 --> 01:17:48.289
- He's right outside.
- He is?

939
01:17:48.373 --> 01:17:51.417
Yeah, he wanted to meet you, officially.

940
01:17:53.962 --> 01:17:56.548
All right. Bring him in.

941
01:17:58.299 --> 01:18:02.136
Could you be nice? He's--
He's important.

942
01:18:14.315 --> 01:18:15.900
Chief Swan.

943
01:18:15.984 --> 01:18:19.320
I want to formally introduce myself.
I'm Edward Cullen.

944
01:18:19.404 --> 01:18:20.738
Hi, Edward.

945
01:18:21.739 --> 01:18:23.050
Bella won't be out too late tonight.

946
01:18:23.074 --> 01:18:25.410
She's just gonna play baseball
with my family.

947
01:18:25.493 --> 01:18:27.745
- Baseball?
- Yes, sir, that's the plan.

948
01:18:27.829 --> 01:18:30.540
Bella's gonna play baseball.

949
01:18:31.875 --> 01:18:33.585
Well, good luck with that.

950
01:18:33.668 --> 01:18:35.712
I'll take good care of her. I promise.

951
01:18:39.507 --> 01:18:40.633
Hey.

952
01:18:41.843 --> 01:18:45.263
- Still got that pepper spray?
- Yeah, Dad.

953
01:18:50.518 --> 01:18:53.229
And since when do
vampires like baseball?

954
01:18:53.313 --> 01:18:58.651
Well, it's the American pastime,
and there's a thunderstorm coming.

955
01:18:58.735 --> 01:19:01.446
It's the only time we can play.
You'll see why.

956
01:19:14.709 --> 01:19:15.752
Hey.

957
01:19:15.835 --> 01:19:17.795
Glad you're here.
We need an umpire.

958
01:19:17.879 --> 01:19:20.757
- She thinks we cheat.
- I know you cheat.

959
01:19:22.967 --> 01:19:25.511
- Call them as you see them, Bella.
- Okay.

960
01:19:35.438 --> 01:19:36.439
It's time.

961
01:19:44.822 --> 01:19:47.033
Okay, now I see why
you need the thunder.

962
01:19:52.580 --> 01:19:55.333
That's gotta be
a home run, right?

963
01:19:55.416 --> 01:19:56.751
Edward's very fast.

964
01:20:05.593 --> 01:20:06.970
Come home, Rosalie!

965
01:20:10.390 --> 01:20:12.016
- You're out.
- Out! Whoo!

966
01:20:13.518 --> 01:20:15.520
Babe, come on. It's just a game.

967
01:20:21.192 --> 01:20:22.276
Nice kitty.

968
01:20:43.673 --> 01:20:44.841
What are you doing?

969
01:21:03.359 --> 01:21:05.319
My monkey man.

970
01:21:19.208 --> 01:21:20.209
Stop!

971
01:21:37.185 --> 01:21:39.896
They were leaving.
Then they heard us.

972
01:21:39.979 --> 01:21:41.481
- Let's go.
- It's too late.

973
01:21:43.483 --> 01:21:44.901
Get your hair down.

974
01:21:46.527 --> 01:21:49.030
Like that'll help. I can smell her
from across the field.

975
01:21:56.079 --> 01:21:58.122
I shouldn't have brought you here.
I'm so sorry.

976
01:21:58.206 --> 01:22:00.792
- What? What--
- Just be quiet and stand behind me.

977
01:22:23.231 --> 01:22:24.816
I believe this belongs to you.

978
01:22:28.736 --> 01:22:29.779
Thank you.

979
01:22:29.862 --> 01:22:31.697
I am Laurent.

980
01:22:31.781 --> 01:22:35.201
And this is Victoria

981
01:22:35.284 --> 01:22:36.702
and James.

982
01:22:37.870 --> 01:22:39.956
I'm Carlisle.
This is my family.

983
01:22:42.083 --> 01:22:43.334
Hello.

984
01:22:43.417 --> 01:22:47.255
I'm afraid your hunting activities
have caused something of a mess for us.

985
01:22:47.338 --> 01:22:51.551
Our apologies. We didn't realize the
territory had been claimed.

986
01:22:51.634 --> 01:22:56.264
Yes, well, we maintain a permanent
residence nearby.

987
01:22:57.306 --> 01:22:58.558
Really?

988
01:23:00.560 --> 01:23:06.190
Well, we won't be a problem anymore.
We were just passing through.

989
01:23:06.274 --> 01:23:09.402
The humans were tracking us,
but we led them east.

990
01:23:09.485 --> 01:23:10.695
You should be safe.

991
01:23:11.821 --> 01:23:12.864
Excellent.

992
01:23:14.157 --> 01:23:17.702
So, could you use
three more players?

993
01:23:20.079 --> 01:23:21.956
Oh, come on. Just one game.

994
01:23:22.039 --> 01:23:24.834
Sure. Why not?

995
01:23:24.917 --> 01:23:27.086
A few of us were leaving.
You could take their place.

996
01:23:27.170 --> 01:23:29.213
We'll bat first.

997
01:23:30.339 --> 01:23:31.899
I'm the one with the wicked curve ball.

998
01:23:32.717 --> 01:23:35.761
- Well, I think we can handle that.
- Oh...

999
01:23:35.845 --> 01:23:38.014
We shall see.

1000
01:23:58.326 --> 01:23:59.785
You brought a snack.

1001
01:24:02.788 --> 01:24:03.873
A human?

1002
01:24:07.501 --> 01:24:09.295
The girl is with us.

1003
01:24:09.378 --> 01:24:10.922
I think it best if you leave.

1004
01:24:15.343 --> 01:24:16.677
I can see the game is over.

1005
01:24:16.761 --> 01:24:19.055
We'll go now.

1006
01:24:21.849 --> 01:24:22.850
James.

1007
01:24:35.738 --> 01:24:37.406
Get Bella out of here.

1008
01:24:37.490 --> 01:24:38.866
Go.

1009
01:24:49.418 --> 01:24:51.712
Okay, I've got it!
I've got it! I'm all right!

1010
01:24:54.131 --> 01:24:55.883
What, now he's coming after me?

1011
01:25:06.435 --> 01:25:07.853
Listen to me. James is a tracker.

1012
01:25:07.937 --> 01:25:10.231
The hunt is his obsession.
I read his mind.

1013
01:25:10.314 --> 01:25:11.983
My reaction on the field set him off.

1014
01:25:12.066 --> 01:25:15.820
I just made this his most exciting
game ever.

1015
01:25:15.903 --> 01:25:17.130
- He's never gonna stop.
- What should we do?

1016
01:25:17.154 --> 01:25:20.074
We have to kill him. Rip him apart
and burn the pieces.

1017
01:25:21.158 --> 01:25:22.618
- Where we going?
- Away from Forks.

1018
01:25:22.702 --> 01:25:23.953
We'll get a ferry to Vancouver.

1019
01:25:24.036 --> 01:25:25.579
I have to go home. Now.

1020
01:25:25.663 --> 01:25:29.083
- You have to take me home.
- You can't go home.

1021
01:25:29.166 --> 01:25:32.145
He's just gonna trace your scent there.
It's the first place he's gonna look.

1022
01:25:32.169 --> 01:25:34.213
- But my dad is there. We...
- It doesn't matter!

1023
01:25:34.297 --> 01:25:36.299
Yes, it does! He could get killed
because of us!

1024
01:25:38.676 --> 01:25:40.445
Just let me get you
out of here first, all right?

1025
01:25:40.469 --> 01:25:43.180
It's my dad!
We have to go back!

1026
01:25:43.264 --> 01:25:45.158
We'll figure a way to lead the tracker
away somehow.

1027
01:25:45.182 --> 01:25:46.822
I don't know. But we have to
do something.

1028
01:25:52.982 --> 01:25:55.609
- Edward, I said leave me alone.
- Bella, don't do this, please.

1029
01:25:55.693 --> 01:25:57.278
It's over! Get out!

1030
01:25:57.361 --> 01:26:00.698
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Bella? What's going on?

1031
01:26:01.699 --> 01:26:04.618
I just gotta get out of here.
I'm leaving now.

1032
01:26:06.746 --> 01:26:07.913
Hey.

1033
01:26:10.958 --> 01:26:12.626
Bella?

1034
01:26:12.710 --> 01:26:16.380
What am I gonna say to him?
I can't hurt him.

1035
01:26:17.381 --> 01:26:20.885
- Bella, what's going on?
- You just have to.

1036
01:26:20.968 --> 01:26:22.178
I'll be down at the truck.

1037
01:26:28.309 --> 01:26:30.561
Did he hurt you?

1038
01:26:30.644 --> 01:26:31.854
No.

1039
01:26:34.148 --> 01:26:38.527
- Break up with you or something?
- No, I broke up with him.

1040
01:26:40.946 --> 01:26:47.370
- I thought you liked him.
- Yeah, that's why I have to leave.

1041
01:26:47.453 --> 01:26:50.122
I don't want this.
I have to go home.

1042
01:26:51.957 --> 01:26:55.294
Home? Your-- your mom's
not even in Phoenix.

1043
01:26:55.378 --> 01:26:57.630
She'll come home.
I'll call her from the road.

1044
01:26:57.713 --> 01:27:01.425
You're not gonna drive home right now.
You can sleep on it.

1045
01:27:01.509 --> 01:27:04.429
If you still feel like going in the
morning, I'll take you to the airport.

1046
01:27:04.512 --> 01:27:08.015
No. I want to drive.
It'll give me more time to think.

1047
01:27:08.099 --> 01:27:10.893
I mean, if I get really tired,
I'll pull into a motel. I promise.

1048
01:27:10.976 --> 01:27:15.689
Look, Bella, I know I'm not that much fun
to be around, but I can change that.

1049
01:27:15.773 --> 01:27:18.401
We can do more stuff together.

1050
01:27:21.612 --> 01:27:25.074
Like what?
Like watch baseball on the flat-screen?

1051
01:27:26.075 --> 01:27:28.536
Eat at the diner every night?
Steak and cobbler?

1052
01:27:28.619 --> 01:27:30.663
Dad, that's you.
That's not me.

1053
01:27:34.458 --> 01:27:37.920
Bella, come on, I just...
I just got you back.

1054
01:27:41.257 --> 01:27:43.384
Yeah, and, you know,
if I don't get out now,

1055
01:27:43.467 --> 01:27:45.678
then I'm just gonna be
stuck here like Mom.

1056
01:28:10.870 --> 01:28:12.955
Your father's gonna forgive you.

1057
01:28:14.623 --> 01:28:16.542
Why don't you let me drive?

1058
01:28:22.631 --> 01:28:23.966
He won't.

1059
01:28:25.176 --> 01:28:27.219
You should've seen his face.

1060
01:28:29.138 --> 01:28:32.600
I told him the same thing that my mom told
him when she was leaving him.

1061
01:28:32.683 --> 01:28:34.935
It's the only way he'd let you go.

1062
01:28:38.022 --> 01:28:39.482
Just don't worry about him now.

1063
01:28:39.565 --> 01:28:42.359
He's safe.
The tracker's following us.

1064
01:28:43.694 --> 01:28:46.113
Oh, God.

1065
01:28:46.197 --> 01:28:48.157
It's just Emmett.

1066
01:28:49.492 --> 01:28:51.535
Alice is in the car behind us.

1067
01:29:13.474 --> 01:29:14.808
Wait.

1068
01:29:15.809 --> 01:29:18.229
He came to warn us about James.

1069
01:29:18.312 --> 01:29:22.525
This isn't my fight,
and I've grown tired of his games,

1070
01:29:22.608 --> 01:29:25.528
but he's got unparalleled senses,
absolutely lethal.

1071
01:29:25.611 --> 01:29:28.614
I've never seen anything like him
in my 300 years.

1072
01:29:28.697 --> 01:29:32.618
And the woman, Victoria,
don't underestimate her.

1073
01:29:37.790 --> 01:29:39.851
I've had to fight our kind before.
We're not easy to kill.

1074
01:29:39.875 --> 01:29:42.169
But not impossible.

1075
01:29:42.253 --> 01:29:44.338
We'll tear them apart
and burn the pieces.

1076
01:29:44.421 --> 01:29:46.358
I don't relish the thought
of killing another creature,

1077
01:29:46.382 --> 01:29:48.884
even a sadistic one like James.

1078
01:29:48.968 --> 01:29:50.844
What if he kills one of us first?

1079
01:29:50.928 --> 01:29:53.568
I'm gonna run Bella south. Can you lead
the tracker away from here?

1080
01:29:53.597 --> 01:29:55.575
No, Edward. James knows you would never
leave Bella.

1081
01:29:55.599 --> 01:29:57.810
- He'll follow you.
- I'll go with Bella.

1082
01:29:57.893 --> 01:29:59.728
Jasper and I
will drive her south.

1083
01:29:59.812 --> 01:30:01.313
I'll keep her safe, Edward.

1084
01:30:01.397 --> 01:30:04.358
- Can you keep your thoughts to yourself?
- Yes.

1085
01:30:08.153 --> 01:30:11.031
Rosalie, Esme,

1086
01:30:11.115 --> 01:30:15.744
could you put these on
so the tracker will pick up Bella's scent?

1087
01:30:17.454 --> 01:30:19.832
Why? What is she to me?

1088
01:30:19.915 --> 01:30:24.503
Rosalie, Bella is with Edward.
She's part of this family now.

1089
01:30:26.589 --> 01:30:28.507
And we protect our family.

1090
01:30:46.233 --> 01:30:49.653
Oh, God. If anything--
What if--

1091
01:30:49.737 --> 01:30:53.574
- If anything happens, I swear to God...
- Nothing's gonna happen.

1092
01:30:53.657 --> 01:30:56.327
There's seven of us,
and there's two of them,

1093
01:30:56.410 --> 01:31:00.080
and when everything's done,
I'm gonna come back and get you.

1094
01:31:00.164 --> 01:31:01.957
Yeah.

1095
01:31:02.041 --> 01:31:04.251
Bella, you are my life now.

1096
01:31:21.852 --> 01:31:25.606
Hey, Mom, it's me again. You must have
let your phone die or something.

1097
01:31:25.689 --> 01:31:30.027
I'm not in Forks, but everything's okay,
and I'll explain it later.

1098
01:31:37.201 --> 01:31:38.661
Rosalie, mark the tree.

1099
01:31:41.372 --> 01:31:42.456
That's good.

1100
01:32:30.129 --> 01:32:32.548
What is it? What do you see?

1101
01:32:44.184 --> 01:32:46.061
He's figured it out.

1102
01:32:46.145 --> 01:32:49.481
The tracker,
he just changed course.

1103
01:32:50.566 --> 01:32:52.484
- Where will it take him, Alice?
- Mirrors.

1104
01:32:52.568 --> 01:32:53.944
A room full of mirrors.

1105
01:32:58.449 --> 01:33:00.534
Edward said the visions
weren't always certain.

1106
01:33:01.618 --> 01:33:03.555
She sees the course people
are on while they're on it.

1107
01:33:03.579 --> 01:33:06.081
If they change their minds,
the vision changes.

1108
01:33:06.165 --> 01:33:11.754
Okay, so the course that the tracker's on
now is gonna lead him to a ballet studio?

1109
01:33:11.837 --> 01:33:15.549
- You've been here?
- I took lessons as a kid.

1110
01:33:15.632 --> 01:33:17.512
The school I went to
had an arch just like that.

1111
01:33:17.593 --> 01:33:19.511
- Was your school here in Phoenix?
- Yeah.

1112
01:33:21.889 --> 01:33:23.809
- Edward, are you okay?
- We've lost the tracker.

1113
01:33:23.891 --> 01:33:25.350
The woman's still in the area.

1114
01:33:25.434 --> 01:33:28.228
Rosalie and Esme are going back to Forks
to protect your father.

1115
01:33:28.312 --> 01:33:34.026
I'm coming to get you. Then you and I
are gonna go somewhere alone.

1116
01:33:34.109 --> 01:33:35.819
And the others will keep hunting.

1117
01:33:35.903 --> 01:33:38.697
I'll do whatever it takes
to make you safe again.

1118
01:33:50.626 --> 01:33:53.212
Hey, Mom,
I'm glad you got my message.

1119
01:33:53.295 --> 01:33:54.630
What are you doing home?

1120
01:33:54.713 --> 01:33:58.091
Bella? Bella?
Bella, where are you?

1121
01:33:58.175 --> 01:34:01.094
- Calm down, everything's fine.
- Bella? Bella?

1122
01:34:01.178 --> 01:34:04.765
I'll explain everything later.
Mom, are you there?

1123
01:34:04.848 --> 01:34:08.894
Forks High School doesn't protect its
students' privacy very well.

1124
01:34:08.977 --> 01:34:13.065
It was just too easy for Victoria to find
your previous address.

1125
01:34:13.148 --> 01:34:15.776
It's a nice house you have here.

1126
01:34:15.859 --> 01:34:19.238
I was prepared to wait for you,
but then Mom came home

1127
01:34:19.321 --> 01:34:23.450
after she received a very
worried call from your dad,

1128
01:34:23.534 --> 01:34:25.661
and it all worked out quite well.

1129
01:34:26.662 --> 01:34:29.122
- Wait, wait...
- Don't touch her! Don't--

1130
01:34:29.206 --> 01:34:31.542
- You can still save her.
- Don't!

1131
01:34:31.625 --> 01:34:33.919
But you're gonna have to get away
from your friends.

1132
01:34:34.002 --> 01:34:35.546
Can you handle that?

1133
01:34:35.629 --> 01:34:38.966
Where should I meet you?

1134
01:34:39.049 --> 01:34:41.176
How about your old ballet studio?

1135
01:34:42.177 --> 01:34:44.304
And I'll know if you bring anyone along.

1136
01:34:47.015 --> 01:34:49.935
You poor Mommy would pay the price
for that mistake.

1137
01:35:07.244 --> 01:35:09.746
I'd never given much thought
to how I would die.

1138
01:35:11.081 --> 01:35:15.043
But dying in the place of someone I love
seems like a good way to go.

1139
01:35:23.510 --> 01:35:25.220
I can't bring myself to regret

1140
01:35:25.304 --> 01:35:28.181
the decisions that brought me
face-to-face with death.

1141
01:35:28.265 --> 01:35:30.225
They also brought me to Edward.

1142
01:35:59.504 --> 01:36:02.716
Bella? Bella?
Bella, where are you?

1143
01:36:02.799 --> 01:36:04.051
- Mom?
- Bella?

1144
01:36:04.134 --> 01:36:05.677
- Mom?
- There you are.

1145
01:36:05.761 --> 01:36:07.220
What are you doing in here?

1146
01:36:07.304 --> 01:36:08.805
Everyone makes fun of me.

1147
01:36:10.015 --> 01:36:12.184
Come on, you're a wonderful dancer.

1148
01:36:12.267 --> 01:36:14.853
Mom, I suck.

1149
01:36:14.937 --> 01:36:18.649
You do not suck.

1150
01:36:27.866 --> 01:36:29.368
That's my favorite part.

1151
01:36:31.161 --> 01:36:34.456
You were a stubborn child,
weren't you? Hmm?

1152
01:36:35.624 --> 01:36:37.542
- She's not even here.
- No.

1153
01:36:40.045 --> 01:36:41.755
Sorry.

1154
01:36:41.838 --> 01:36:44.925
You know, but you really
made it too easy.

1155
01:36:45.008 --> 01:36:48.971
So to make things
more entertaining,

1156
01:36:49.054 --> 01:36:51.807
I'm gonna make a little film
of our time together.

1157
01:36:53.725 --> 01:36:57.104
I borrowed this from your house.
I hope you don't mind.

1158
01:36:57.187 --> 01:36:59.481
Good. And...

1159
01:37:00.941 --> 01:37:02.526
action.

1160
01:37:04.695 --> 01:37:06.405
That'll break Edward's little heart.

1161
01:37:06.488 --> 01:37:08.824
You have... Edward has
nothing to do with this!

1162
01:37:08.907 --> 01:37:11.535
But he does.

1163
01:37:11.618 --> 01:37:14.287
Oh, his rage will make
for more interesting sport

1164
01:37:14.371 --> 01:37:17.833
than his... oh, his feeble attempt
to protect you.

1165
01:37:19.126 --> 01:37:20.585
And let's continue.

1166
01:37:36.101 --> 01:37:39.980
Beautiful. Very visually dynamic.

1167
01:37:42.399 --> 01:37:44.317
I chose my stage well.

1168
01:37:49.656 --> 01:37:52.492
It's too bad he didn't have
the strength to turn you.

1169
01:37:53.493 --> 01:37:56.204
Instead, he kept you
this fragile little human.

1170
01:37:56.288 --> 01:37:57.998
It's cruel, really.

1171
01:38:02.919 --> 01:38:04.463
Tell Edward how much it hurts.

1172
01:38:05.547 --> 01:38:07.299
Tell him to avenge you. Tell him!

1173
01:38:07.382 --> 01:38:09.801
- No, Edward, don't!
- Tell him! Tell him!

1174
01:38:22.814 --> 01:38:26.777
You're alone 'cause you're faster
than the others.

1175
01:38:28.320 --> 01:38:30.322
But not stronger.

1176
01:38:31.531 --> 01:38:33.700
I'm strong enough to kill you.

1177
01:38:40.791 --> 01:38:41.833
I'm sorry.

1178
01:39:46.273 --> 01:39:47.482
Bella, Bella, it's okay.

1179
01:39:47.566 --> 01:39:50.110
Son. Enough.

1180
01:39:50.193 --> 01:39:52.362
Remember who you are.

1181
01:39:57.576 --> 01:40:00.120
- Bella, you're okay.
- Bella needs you.

1182
01:40:01.121 --> 01:40:02.789
It's okay. It's okay.

1183
01:40:02.873 --> 01:40:04.124
Oh, God.

1184
01:40:08.003 --> 01:40:09.921
Carlisle? Her blood.

1185
01:40:10.005 --> 01:40:11.566
- Your brothers will take care of him.
- I got him.

1186
01:40:11.590 --> 01:40:12.883
- Carlisle!
- Start the fire.

1187
01:40:12.966 --> 01:40:14.384
Get the floorboards.

1188
01:40:15.927 --> 01:40:18.388
- Alice!
- Alice, go.

1189
01:40:27.981 --> 01:40:30.084
Her femoral artery's been severed.
She's losing too much blood.

1190
01:40:30.108 --> 01:40:32.194
No, no, my hand is burning!

1191
01:40:33.862 --> 01:40:35.197
It's the venom.

1192
01:40:36.448 --> 01:40:39.075
You have to make a choice.
You could let the change happen.

1193
01:40:40.285 --> 01:40:41.286
No.

1194
01:40:42.287 --> 01:40:43.538
No.

1195
01:40:44.831 --> 01:40:46.458
It's gonna happen, Edward.
I've seen it.

1196
01:40:46.541 --> 01:40:49.628
- It doesn't have to be that way.
- She's still hemorrhaging.

1197
01:40:49.711 --> 01:40:51.546
Alice, make me a tourniquet.
Your belt.

1198
01:40:51.630 --> 01:40:53.924
Carlisle, what's my other option?

1199
01:40:55.217 --> 01:40:57.302
Tie it above my hands.

1200
01:40:57.385 --> 01:40:58.595
Carlisle!

1201
01:41:00.722 --> 01:41:01.848
Go.

1202
01:41:06.561 --> 01:41:07.788
We could try to suck the venom out.

1203
01:41:07.812 --> 01:41:10.941
- You know I won't be able to stop.
- Then find the will to stop.

1204
01:41:12.609 --> 01:41:15.195
But choose.
She only has minutes left.

1205
01:41:18.490 --> 01:41:19.810
I'm gonna make it go away, Bella.

1206
01:41:23.370 --> 01:41:24.913
I'm gonna make it go away.

1207
01:41:43.765 --> 01:41:45.016
Edward, stop.

1208
01:41:45.100 --> 01:41:47.018
Her blood is clean.
You're killing her.

1209
01:41:48.019 --> 01:41:49.437
Edward.

1210
01:41:49.521 --> 01:41:50.939
Stop.

1211
01:41:52.023 --> 01:41:53.733
Stop.

1212
01:41:54.859 --> 01:41:56.403
Find the will.

1213
01:42:20.969 --> 01:42:24.764
Death is peaceful, easy.

1214
01:42:31.604 --> 01:42:34.107
Life is harder.

1215
01:42:38.820 --> 01:42:39.946
Bella?

1216
01:42:42.115 --> 01:42:43.158
Baby?

1217
01:42:44.951 --> 01:42:46.161
Bella.

1218
01:42:47.996 --> 01:42:49.664
- Mom?
- Hey.

1219
01:42:49.748 --> 01:42:52.834
Where is he? Where's...

1220
01:42:53.835 --> 01:42:56.171
- Where's Edward?
- He's asleep.

1221
01:42:58.006 --> 01:43:01.468
He never leaves. And your dad,
he's down at the cafeteria.

1222
01:43:02.844 --> 01:43:04.971
What happened?

1223
01:43:05.055 --> 01:43:10.185
Well, when you fell, you broke your leg,
and you lost a lot of blood.

1224
01:43:11.519 --> 01:43:13.688
You don't remember
any of this, do you?

1225
01:43:15.857 --> 01:43:20.070
Edward came down with his dad to try
to convince you to come back to Forks.

1226
01:43:20.153 --> 01:43:23.490
So you went over to their hotel,
and then you tripped,

1227
01:43:23.573 --> 01:43:26.951
and you fell down
two flights of stairs.

1228
01:43:27.035 --> 01:43:28.244
Went through a window!

1229
01:43:35.126 --> 01:43:36.961
Yeah, that sounds like me.

1230
01:43:37.045 --> 01:43:39.214
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

1231
01:43:43.134 --> 01:43:46.221
It's Phil. He's so worried about you.

1232
01:43:48.598 --> 01:43:51.267
- You're texting.
- Finally, yeah.

1233
01:43:53.728 --> 01:43:55.397
I told him to stay down in Florida.

1234
01:43:55.480 --> 01:43:57.899
Honey, you are gonna love Jacksonville.

1235
01:43:57.982 --> 01:44:01.486
It's sunny every day, and we found
the cutest little house,

1236
01:44:01.569 --> 01:44:02.849
and you've got
your own bathroom.

1237
01:44:02.904 --> 01:44:04.531
Mom, I still want to live in Forks.

1238
01:44:06.074 --> 01:44:07.659
What?

1239
01:44:07.742 --> 01:44:09.077
I want to live in Forks.

1240
01:44:10.078 --> 01:44:12.539
Well, okay, but we'll talk about it.

1241
01:44:14.207 --> 01:44:16.835
Do you mind getting Dad?

1242
01:44:16.918 --> 01:44:19.754
I have to talk to him.
Apologize.

1243
01:44:19.838 --> 01:44:22.674
Okay, baby. I'll go get him.

1244
01:44:23.675 --> 01:44:26.386
- And I'll go get a nurse, okay?
- Okay.

1245
01:44:38.314 --> 01:44:41.443
So what happened?
Where's James?

1246
01:44:43.069 --> 01:44:44.487
We took care of it.

1247
01:44:51.536 --> 01:44:53.580
And the woman,
Victoria, she ran off.

1248
01:44:54.706 --> 01:44:56.666
I'm alive because of you.

1249
01:44:56.749 --> 01:44:59.252
No, you're in here because of me.

1250
01:45:00.879 --> 01:45:06.551
The worst part of it was that I thought
I wasn't gonna be able to stop.

1251
01:45:07.552 --> 01:45:08.928
You did stop.

1252
01:45:10.805 --> 01:45:14.767
Bella, you gotta go to Jacksonville
so I can't hurt you anymore.

1253
01:45:16.769 --> 01:45:17.937
What?

1254
01:45:21.107 --> 01:45:23.818
Are you... No! No!

1255
01:45:26.321 --> 01:45:28.072
I don't even know
what you're-- How--

1256
01:45:28.156 --> 01:45:30.950
What are you talking about?
You want me to go away? I can't--

1257
01:45:31.034 --> 01:45:33.578
No, I can't--
I can't just leave you--

1258
01:45:33.661 --> 01:45:34.704
I know.

1259
01:45:36.873 --> 01:45:39.751
We can't be apart.
You can't leave me.

1260
01:45:40.960 --> 01:45:42.295
I'm here.

1261
01:45:45.840 --> 01:45:50.970
Okay, just don't-- You just can't say
stuff like that to me. Ever.

1262
01:45:54.974 --> 01:45:58.269
Where else am I gonna go?

1263
01:46:47.735 --> 01:46:51.531
Alice lent me the dress.
The cast is...

1264
01:46:52.991 --> 01:46:53.992
You're perfect.

1265
01:46:57.370 --> 01:46:59.539
I'll take care of her, Chief Swan.

1266
01:46:59.622 --> 01:47:02.125
Uh-huh. I've heard that before.

1267
01:47:06.671 --> 01:47:08.172
All right, Bells.

1268
01:47:10.592 --> 01:47:13.177
I put a new can
of pepper spray in your bag.

1269
01:47:13.261 --> 01:47:14.554
Dad.

1270
01:47:14.637 --> 01:47:16.180
And, uh...

1271
01:47:18.224 --> 01:47:20.893
Well, you look beautiful.

1272
01:47:22.770 --> 01:47:23.771
Thanks.

1273
01:47:25.773 --> 01:47:27.025
- See you.
- Yeah.

1274
01:47:34.157 --> 01:47:37.285
Hey. I'll be right back.

1275
01:47:39.662 --> 01:47:41.122
- Bella.
- Jacob.

1276
01:47:42.290 --> 01:47:44.959
- Hey.
- Nice.

1277
01:47:45.960 --> 01:47:47.211
You, too.

1278
01:47:47.295 --> 01:47:49.855
Are you crashing the prom or something?
Did you come with a date?

1279
01:47:50.590 --> 01:47:51.591
No.

1280
01:47:56.054 --> 01:47:58.765
My dad paid me to come talk to you.

1281
01:47:58.848 --> 01:48:03.186
- Twenty bucks.
- Let's hear it.

1282
01:48:03.269 --> 01:48:04.937
Just don't get mad, okay?

1283
01:48:06.898 --> 01:48:09.233
He wants you to break up
with your boyfriend.

1284
01:48:10.234 --> 01:48:16.157
It's just, he said, quote,
"We'll be watching you."

1285
01:48:17.158 --> 01:48:19.702
Okay, well, tell him, "Thanks."

1286
01:48:19.786 --> 01:48:21.329
Okay.

1287
01:48:21.412 --> 01:48:24.499
- And to pay up.
- Okay. Oh, let me help you.

1288
01:48:24.582 --> 01:48:27.460
Jacob. I'll take it from here.

1289
01:48:31.547 --> 01:48:33.007
Guess I'll see you around, Bella.

1290
01:48:35.802 --> 01:48:36.886
All right.

1291
01:48:44.143 --> 01:48:47.313
I leave you alone for two minutes,
and the wolves descend.

1292
01:48:54.821 --> 01:48:56.298
I can't believe you're making me do this.

1293
01:48:56.322 --> 01:48:57.532
Just smile.

1294
01:49:18.344 --> 01:49:21.305
Wow. You are really trying to kill me.

1295
01:49:21.389 --> 01:49:23.391
The prom is an important
rite of passage.

1296
01:49:23.474 --> 01:49:25.935
I didn't want you to miss anything.

1297
01:49:26.018 --> 01:49:27.186
Oh.

1298
01:49:53.963 --> 01:49:54.964
Bella, hey!

1299
01:49:58.676 --> 01:50:00.762
- Do you want to go?
- Yeah.

1300
01:50:00.845 --> 01:50:03.556
All right, slowing it down.

1301
01:50:09.103 --> 01:50:11.689
Shall we?

1302
01:50:11.773 --> 01:50:13.399
You're serious?

1303
01:50:14.525 --> 01:50:16.277
Oh, why not?

1304
01:50:31.501 --> 01:50:34.712
See, you're dancing.

1305
01:50:34.796 --> 01:50:36.255
At prom.

1306
01:50:57.193 --> 01:50:59.612
Edward, why did you save me?

1307
01:50:59.695 --> 01:51:04.200
If you just let the venom spread,
I could be like you by now.

1308
01:51:06.744 --> 01:51:10.039
You don't know
what you're saying.

1309
01:51:10.122 --> 01:51:12.542
- You don't want this.
- I want you.

1310
01:51:12.625 --> 01:51:14.001
Always.

1311
01:51:19.549 --> 01:51:22.009
I'm not gonna end your life for you.

1312
01:51:22.093 --> 01:51:25.179
I'm dying already.

1313
01:51:26.639 --> 01:51:28.516
Every second, I get closer.

1314
01:51:29.600 --> 01:51:33.479
- Older.
- That's the way it's supposed to be.

1315
01:51:34.772 --> 01:51:37.233
Alice said that she saw me like you.

1316
01:51:37.316 --> 01:51:39.652
- I heard her.
- Her visions change.

1317
01:51:39.735 --> 01:51:41.988
Yeah, based on what people decide.

1318
01:51:42.989 --> 01:51:43.990
I've decided.

1319
01:51:47.952 --> 01:51:51.956
So that's what you dream about.
Becoming a monster.

1320
01:51:55.835 --> 01:51:58.045
I dream about being with you forever.

1321
01:51:59.046 --> 01:52:00.590
Forever?

1322
01:52:05.303 --> 01:52:07.430
And you're ready right now?

1323
01:52:09.473 --> 01:52:10.641
Yes.

1324
01:52:27.700 --> 01:52:32.246
Is it not enough just to have a long
and happy life with me?

1325
01:52:39.837 --> 01:52:43.966
Yeah. For now.

1326
01:53:12.411 --> 01:53:17.291
No one will surrender tonight,
but I won't give in.

1327
01:53:19.085 --> 01:53:21.587
I know what I want.

